About:
['I support businesses in all things legal related to technology and data, whether your developing your own solutions, implementing someone else’s, or somewhere between the two!

Starting from a place of ensuring that your use of technology doesn’t result in a risk to your business, and moving on from there to ensure that you can harness all of the advantages that technology can bring in a compliant manner, I’m well versed in e-commerce and adtech, digitisation, cloud and SaaS solutions, disruptive tech, big data and artificial intelligence/machine learning.

Support I can provide includes:
- assessing legal compliance of business solutions (whether that be the implementation of technology, outsourcing or other business processes) and working with teams to balance risk appropriately;
- supporting ongoing data protection compliance by means of policies, impact assessments and regular reviews;
- managing crisis situations, including data breaches, exercise of individual rights regarding data and regulator investigations;
- developing contracting structures and negotiating agreements, focussing on what your business needs;
- developing or reviewing user, customer or consumer journeys with an understanding of the compliance requirements and technical opportunities/limitations.

I’m a great communicator and trainer with a genuine passion for technology and data protection. My training sessions get fantastic feedback, whether they take the more formal “chalk and talk” approach or are more informal roundtables (or currently, virtual roundtables) where teams can share their experience and obtain expert advice in one shot!

Views expressed on LinkedIn are my own and not views of ESI. Shares or likes not endorsement.']

